    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ Gas 6</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chunky chips, then strip the <strong>rosemary leaves </strong>from their stalks and chop them roughly</p><p>Add the<strong> chips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, a generous pinch of both <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and sprinkle over the<strong> chopped rosemary</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden</p>",
